Description: Stem and foot sherd of possibly South Ionian pottery cup with everted rim; exterior glazed black; reserved on underside; inscription on underside.
Type series: Vallet and Villard Ionian Cup Type B3
Curator's comments: The number in Petrie's catalogue, 373, is written in ink on the underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 373)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.510) (Phase 3)
